@meta
title: {{TITLE}}
version: {{VERSION}}
owner: {{OWNER}}
doc_base_path:

@map
- LOG-000 | Document Guide | Define implementation-flow scope and downstream detail docs
- LOG-001 | End-to-End Pipeline | Define processing order from input to user output
- LOG-010 | Step Processing | Define input, output, and failure handling per step
- LOG-020 | Public/Admin Flow | Separate user-facing and operator-facing flows
- LOG-030 | Batch and Automation | Define scheduled runs, correction, promotion, and rollback
- LOG-040 | Implementation Priority | Define migration order from current to target structure
- LOG-050 | Maintenance Structure | Define change points and ownership boundaries

@section LOG-000
title: Document Guide
{
	summary: Implementation discussion starts here
	path:
	links: GUIDE-INPUT
	content:
	<<<
	[Question this document answers]
	- In which order does this project process data and publish output?

	[Next documents]
	- data/storage contracts: 03
	- automation/strategy: 04
	- operations/exceptions: 05
	- implementation order: 06
	>>>
}

@section LOG-001
title: End-to-End Pipeline
{
	summary: Full processing order in one place
	path:
	links: PIPELINE-001
	content:
	<<<
	[Flow]
	1) collect input
	2) normalize
	3) validate
	4) process core logic
	5) persist
	6) publish/respond
	7) observe/correct
	>>>
}

